neighborhood_overview:
We are in the middle of the centre, yet so quiet and peaceful. Just walk through the alley and you find yourself in the middle of vibrating Amsterdam.

The hot spots of Amsterdam, including the popular Waterlooplein flea market, the Opera House, the Red Light District , China Town, Dam Square and Rembrandt Square are all within very short walking distances.

Directly around the corner is the charming Zeedijk. This is the old Dutch sailing quarter with its typical Dutch cafes and breweries, topped up by influences from the journeys to the far East; full of exotic restaurants and shops. The vibrant Nieuwmarkt is perhaps the liveliest square in the city, with the beautiful old building in the middle, that used to serve as a place for weighing goods after having been offloaded from the ships. The Oude Waal area shows the history of Amsterdam with its nautical character, where it all started out in a remote past.

Small street with special little houses in Amsterdam West, one of the most attractive area's in the city. A lot of bars, restaurants and other things to do in the neighborhood, like the great foodhallen.

Only 5 min by bike or tram to the city center, and enjoy the beautiful canals and museum's.

The house is just renovated and offers you everything you want. If you have any questions, please contact me.

name: Private loft next @Vondelpark with PRIVATE parking
description: Vintage & private loft centrally situated in the heart of Amsterdam, next to the famous Vondelpark, Museumplein, Leidseplein and Foodhallen. Consists of 2 separate bedrooms, sleeps 4 persons total, of which one can be made as double room. A bright spacious living room, bathroom and a basic pantry ( no stove), all private! Perfect for two couples or a family interested in Culture. Friendly host who is happy to share his secret city spots.
neighborhood_overview:
Close to the Vondelpark, typical dutch houses, nice ambiance, friendly neighbors. Lots of nice restaurants, pubs and local stores & markets. All the museums, restaurants and terraces are open again.

If you are looking for more tranquil options, you could visit the little fisherman villages like Volendam and Edam. Maybe a round of golf in the area and have beautiful walks or bike rides.

My home is also near to the highway and a great location to venture into all areas around Amsterdam. Visit Utrecht, The Hague, Delft or Den Bosch beautiful historical cities, ALL within 1hr.

Or for the kids there are many attractions around aswell, beach, sailing, horse riding, attractionpark Duinrell, Legoland Discovery Centre, all within 1hr.

name: Ecoluxe accommodation 'The Green Tunnel'
description: Spacious, ground level private ecoluxe two-room accommodation with sweeping views across the water and with bathroom and pantry. Including a charming lush waterside garden and floating terrace with lawn chairs. Your private jetty provides direct access to the natural swimming water. Free parking. Explore new city district IJburg with striking architecture, bustling harbor, many restaurants and shops and a splendid park. The tram around the corner brings you downtown Amsterdam in 15 minutes.
neighborhood_overview:
The accommodation is situated at a canal in Amsterdam-IJburg. This new Amsterdam urban district in is situated on specially constructed islands in 'IJmeer', a lake on the eastern side of Amsterdam, only 15 minutes away from downtown (by tram).
It is one of the largest new developments in the Amsterdam area, with a current population of 20,000. Many tourists who love the combination of fresh and inspiring architecture, water recreation possibilities, beach, nature, good restaurants & hip shops and the bustling marina already discovered IJburg. Discover this new urban district too!
The shopping center with a variety of local shops and restaurants is a 2 minutes walk, the park is a 5 minutes walk and the bustling marine with many restaurants and bars is a 10 minutes walk.
